* You should set up your documentation in a versioned way (perhaps in a Git if it's not already part of a specific project's source code):
> This provides the benefit of being able to review how things have evolved over time and it allows you to go back to see why things may have been a certain way.
* It can be a good idea for documentation to go through a PR and review process like any other code.